# Cline Rules for X-Twitter MCP

## IMPORTANT: X/Twitter Articles Need Playwright

When fetching X/Twitter articles, use the `get_article` MCP tool.
DO NOT use WebFetch or HTTP requests - they will fail because X articles require JavaScript.

Pattern: Any URL like `x.com/*/status/*` or `twitter.com/*/status/*` needs `get_article`.

## Tool Quick Reference

| Task | MCP Tool |
|------|----------|
| Search tweets | `mcp__x-twitter__search_twitter` |
| Read article | `mcp__x-twitter__get_article` (PLAYWRIGHT) |
| Get user | `mcp__x-twitter__get_user_by_screen_name` |
| Get thread | `mcp__x-twitter__get_conversation` |
| Post tweet | `mcp__x-twitter__post_tweet` |
| Like tweet | `mcp__x-twitter__favorite_tweet` |
| Retweet | `mcp__x-twitter__retweet` |

## Profile Permissions

- `researcher`: Read-only (search, get tweets, articles)
- `creator`: + Post, engage
- `manager`: + Follow, block, lists
- `automation`: Full access
